               <msContents>
                  <summary>According to Grenfell and Hunt: "Receipt for 20 drachmae for poll-tax of the thirtieth year, and 10 [obols of copper for prosdiagraphomena], paid by Souchas... dated in the thirty-first year of Marcus Aurelius Commodus."</summary>
                  <msItem>
                     <note type="general">Text is on one side only, 7 lines written with the fibers.  Highly ligatured script.</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="grc">Greek</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
               <physDesc>
                  <p>9.2 x 7.3cm.  Top, left, and bottom margins mostly intact.</p>
               </physDesc>
